The paper deals with lower bounds for arithmetic circuits, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves the study of depth reduction and shifted partial derivatives, which are techniques used in algebraic complexity theory, a subfield of computational complexity theory. This suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.IT (information theory), cs.LO (logic in computer science), and cs.SC (symbolic computation).
